           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01">
 	<p n="1-25">Village of Vyau: Si Śrivatsa, Si Vrahmaśiva, Si Śrivallabha, Gho Kaṁval, Gho Kaṁvai, another Gho Kaṁvai, Gho Śivaśikha, Gho Dharmma, Gho Kantoṅ, Gho Kavit, Gho Kansaṁ, Gho Kanloñ, Gho Vkap, Gho Kañcan, Gho Vidyā, Gho Hari, Gho Pandan, Gho Ravi, another Gho Pandan, Gho Śrīkantha, Gho Taṅkū, Gho Agat, Gho Kapas, Gho Phnos, Gho Lpau, Gho Śri----, Gho Chke, Gho Chnoṅ, Gho Kanleṅ, Gho Hr̥dayabhāva, Gho Kanteṅ, another Gho Kanteṅ, Gho Kañjes, Gho Krau, Gho Kaṁpañ, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Dīrgha, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/> Khñuṁ Gho Kan-as, another Gho Phnos, another Gho Khñuṁ, another Gho Kaṁvai, Gho Śivaputra, another Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kan-añ, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Svasti, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kan-u, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Pandan accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kanhen, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Kaṁpit accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/> Kantū, Tai A Khñuṁ, Tai Kanteṅ <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kanden accomapnied by a son <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/> Panlas accompanied by a son <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>, another Tai Kaṁpit, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, another <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/></p>
              <p n="26-28">Ruined.</p>
              <p n="29-30"><gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Labdha, Tai A Dyāt, Tai Pa<supplied reason="subaudible">ndan</supplied></p>
